  "texts": [
    "The disruption in the supply chain, combined with existing concerns about limited supply, contributed to the upward pressure on oil prices.\"",
    "Question:\"U.S. crude oil futures were up 22 cents at $67.46 as of 10:59 a.m. EDT, while Brent crude fell 14 cents to $72.98.",
    "U.S. gasoline futures fell 0.7 per cent to $2.0724 a gallon.\"",
    "Answer:\"Netural|0.85|The prices of oil are described as unchanged in the article because the changes in the prices of U.S. crude oil futures and Brent crude are relatively small.",
    "Specifically, U.S. crude oil futures increased by 22 cents to $67.46, and Brent crude fell by 14 cents to $72.98."
